---
We present results for the ionic structure in hydrocarbons (polystyrene, polyethylene) that were shock compressed to pressures of up to 190 GPa, inducing rapid melting of the samples.
[Download paper here](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-019-40782-5.pdf)

Recommended citation: N.J. Hartley et al. "Liquid Structure of Shock-Compressed Hydrocarbons at Megabar Pressures" <i>PRL</i> 121 (2018) 245501.
